---
const exampleCode = `# Familiar gem-shaped work
$ pack install
$ pack list rails
$ pack search sidekiq

# Project dependency flows
$ pack add rack-cors
$ pack update rails
$ pack why rack

# Rails-shaped operations
$ pack doctor
$ pack exec rubocop
$ pack db migrate`
---

<section class="sect" id="solution">
  <div class="wrap">

    <p class="sect-eyebrow" data-reveal>The Solution</p>
    <h2 class="sect-heading" data-reveal>Keep the verbs. Tighten the path.</h2>
    <p class="sect-body" data-reveal>
      Pack keeps the commands Ruby developers already expect, then moves the hot path into Rust so dependency work, diagnostics, and Rails helpers stay close together.
    </p>

    <div class="soln-layout" data-reveal>
      <div class="code-preview">
        <pre><code>{exampleCode}</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="points" data-stagger>
        <div class="point">
          <p class="point-name">Native gem verbs</p>
          <p class="point-desc">Install, list, search, inspect, and clean up through a fast native path.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="point">
          <p class="point-name">Parser hot path</p>
          <p class="point-desc">Gemfile and lockfile parsing run in microseconds in the local Criterion benches.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="point">
          <p class="point-name">Project tasking</p>
          <p class="point-desc"><code>Packfile</code> gives teams one place for repeatable dev, test, and maintenance commands.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="point">
          <p class="point-name">Rails helpers</p>
          <p class="point-desc">Server, console, test, db, assets, and Docker helpers live next to dependency work.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .sect {
    padding: var(--sp-24) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .sect-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }

  .sect-heading {
    font-size: clamp(var(--text-2xl), 4vw, var(--text-3xl));
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);
  }

  .sect-body {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
    max-width: 600px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-12);
  }

  .soln-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.05fr 0.95fr;
    gap: var(--sp-10);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .code-preview {
    background: var(--bg-muted);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--sp-6);
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .code-preview pre {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .code-preview code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--fg);
    background: none;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .points {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .point {
    padding: var(--sp-5) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .point:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .point-name {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-1);
  }

  .point-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .point-desc code {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .soln-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .code-preview { padding: var(--sp-4); }
    .code-preview code { font-size: var(--text-xs); }
  }
</style>
